<p>Additionally, for this weekend only, EA is discounting College Football 26's Deluxe edition from $100 to $75. This version of the game comes with a variety of extras, including Ultimate Team credits and more.</p><p>Also, EA Sports <a href="https://x.com/EASPORTSCollege/status/1961086316482875613" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">announced the results</a> of its seasonal sim using College Football 26, with the system determining that Texas will win the national championship come January 2026. This is not a very bold prediction, as Texas is starting the season ranked No. 1, and along with Ohio State, is <a href="https://www.espn.com/college-football/futures" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">considered the betting favorite by many</a> to win the title.</p><p>CFB 26 was the <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/matpiscatella.bsky.social/post/3lxf3jextrc26" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">No. 1 best-selling game for July in the US</a> and is the <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/2025-best-selling-games/2900-6281/" data-ref-id="2900-6281">No. 3 overall best-selling game of 2025 so far in the US. </a></p><p>GameSpot's <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/ea-sports-college-football-26-review-sophomore-success/1900-6418383/" data-ref-id="1900-6418383">CFB 26 review</a> scored the game an 8/10, with reviewer Richard Wakeling writing, "The presentation is excellent, with a fantastic attention to detail that helps differentiate each team."</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
